article.headline: North Florida 62, Florida Gulf Coast 56
article.story: FORT MYERS, Fla. -- Brad Haugabrook scored 14 points as North Florida held off Florida Gulf Coast 62-56 on Friday night. The Ospreys (7-8, 2/3 Atlantic Sun Conference), coming off an 84-79 loss to Mercer on Monday which snapped their five-game winning streak, led 31-23 at halftime. The Eagles (5-9, 2-3) pulled within a point on three occasions in the second half from 9:29 to 7:33, but could get no closer. Trailing 55-53 with 4:22 left, they scored only three points the rest of the way. The Ospreys scored five straight points, including two baskets by Haugabrook, to build a seven-point cushion with 2:11 left. North Florida was 8-for-21 from 3-point range while Florida Gulf Coast was 0-for-10 from long range. Jerron Granberry and Stan Januska scored 12 points each for the Ospreys. Reed Baker led the Eagles with 15 points on 7-for-10 shooting and Anthony Banks added 14 points.
